data.flavorText: In the distant past, they were fairly strong, but they have become gradually weaker over time.

abilities.name: Energy Jump
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may move an Energy card from 1 of your Pokémon to another of your Pokémon. This power can't be used if Alakazam is affected by a Special Condition.

data.name: Exeggcute
data.flavorText: Even though it appears to be eggs of some sort, it was discovered to be a life-form more like plant seeds.

data.name: Exeggcute
data.flavorText: Six of them together form a full-fledged Pokémon. It's often hunted by Crabrawler, but uses psychokinesis to drive it off.

abilities.name: Flare Condition
abilities.text: As long as Arcanine has any Fire Energy attached to it, Arcanine has no Weakness.

data.name: Paras
data.flavorText: Burrows under the ground to gnaw on tree roots. The mushrooms on its back absorb most of the nutrition.

data.name: Arcanine
data.flavorText: A legendary Pokémon famous for its beauty. It looks almost as if it flies when it runs.

data.name: Gyarados
data.flavorText: Rarely seen in the wild. Huge and vicious, it is capable of destroying entire cities in a rage.

abilities.name: Energy Recharge
abilities.text: When you play Arcanine from your hand to evolve your Active Pokémon, you may flip 3 coins. For each heads, choose a basic Energy card from your discard pile and attach it to Arcanine.

data.name: Vileplume

abilities.name: Disgusting Pollen
abilities.text: As long as this Pokémon is your Active Pokémon, your opponent's Basic Pokémon can't attack.

data.flavorText: The larger its petals, the more toxic pollen it contains. Its big head is heavy and hard to hold up.

data.name: Exeggcute
data.flavorText: Six of them form a single Pokémon. Should one of the six be lost, the next morning there will once more be six.

abilities.name: Peal of Thunder
abilities.text: Once during your turn, when you play Charizard from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokémon, you may look at the top 5 cards of your deck, choose as many Energy cards as you like, and attach them to 1 of your Pokémon. Discard the other cards.

data.name: Dark Dugtrio

abilities.name: Sinkhole
abilities.text: Whenever your opponent's Active Pokémon retreats, your opponent flips a coin. If tails, this power does 20 damage to that Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance.) This power stops working while Dark Dugtrio is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.

data.flavorText: Digs large sinkholes in the ground and tries to trap its enemies in them.

data.name: Exeggutor
data.flavorText: It is called "The Walking Jungle." If a head grows too big, it falls off and becomes an Exeggcute.

data.name: Alolan Exeggutor
data.flavorText: As it grew taller and taller, it outgrew its reliance on psychic powers, while within it awakened the power of the sleeping dragon.

data.name: Scyther
data.flavorText: The sharp scythes on its forearms become increasingly sharp by cutting through hard objects.

data.name: Exeggutor
data.flavorText: It is called "The Walking Jungle." If a head grows too big, it falls off and becomes an Exeggcute.

data.name: Gyarados
data.flavorText: Rarely seen in the wild. Huge and vicious, it is capable of destroying entire cities in a rage.

data.name: Charmeleon
data.flavorText: It lashes about with its tail to knock down its foe. It then tears up the fallen opponent with sharp claws.

data.name: Parasect
data.flavorText: The large mushroom on its back controls it. It often fights over territory with Shiinotic.

data.name: Parasect
data.flavorText: The larger the mushroom on its back grows, the stronger the mushroom spores it scatters.

data.name: Parasect

abilities.name: Panic Spores
abilities.text: Put 2 damage counters on your opponent's Confused Pokémon between turns.

data.flavorText: The bug is mostly dead, with the mushroom on its back having become the main body. If the mushroom comes off, the bug stops moving.

data.name: Jigglypuff
data.flavorText: After lulling its enemies with its large eyes, this Pokémon sings them to sleep with a relaxing melody.

abilities.name: Pollen Defense
abilities.text: If an attack does damage to Erika's Vileplume while it's your Active Pokémon (even if it's Knocked Out), flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused. This power works even while Erika's Vileplume is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.

data.name: Bellsprout
data.flavorText: Its bud looks like a human face. Because of the bud, it is rumored to be a type of legendary mandrake plant.

data.name: Scyther
data.flavorText: While young, they live together deep in the mountains, training themselves in how to fight with their scythes and move at high speeds.

abilities.name: Beating Wings
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), if Pidgeot is your Active Pokémon, you may shuffle 1 of your Benched Pokémon and all cards attached to it into your deck. This power can't be used if Pidgeot is affected by a Special Condition.

abilities.name: Sooth Dust
abilities.text: As long as Butterfree is your Active Pokémon, remove 1 damage counter from each of your Pokémon between turns.

data.name: Exeggcute
data.flavorText: Six of them form a single Pokémon. Should one of the six be lost, the next morning there will once more be six.

abilities.name: Type Change
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may choose 1 of the Defending Pokémon. Mew is the same type as that Pokémon (all if that Pokémon is more than 1 type) until the end of your turn. This power can't be used if Mew is affected by a Special Condition.

data.name: Alakazam

abilities.name: Power Cancel
abilities.text: Once during your opponent's turn, when your opponent's Pokémon uses any Poké-Power, you may discard 2 cards from your hand and prevent all effects of that Poké-Power. (This counts as that Pokémon using its Poké-Power.) This power can't be used if Alakazam is affected by a Special Condition.

data.flavorText: Its superb memory lets it recall everything it has experienced from birth. Its IQ exceeds 5,000.

data.name: Dark Raichu
data.flavorText: Stores up electricity in its body, then suddenly releases it to surprise and shock everyone.

data.name: Detective Pikachu
data.flavorText: He loves to show off his vast knowledge. This expressive Pikachu is like a middle-aged man.

data.name: Pinsir
data.flavorText: It swings its long antlers wildly to attack. During cold periods, it hides deep in forests.

data.name: Dark Golbat

abilities.name: Sneak Attack
abilities.text: When you play Dark Golbat from your hand, you may choose 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. If you do, Dark Golbat does 10 damage to that Pokémon. Apply Weakness and Resistance.

data.flavorText: Sneaks up silently on its prey and attacks it from behind, sometimes killing it with one bite.

data.name: Hitmonchan
data.flavorText: While seeming to do nothing, it fires punches in lightning-fast volleys that are impossible to see.

data.name: Butterfree
data.flavorText: The poison scales on its wings are waterproof, allowing this Pokémon to be active even on rainy days.

data.name: Raichu
data.flavorText: If the electric pouches in its cheeks become fully charged, both ears will stand straight up.

data.name: Weepinbell
data.flavorText: It spits out Poison Powder to immobilize the enemy and then finishes it with a spray of Acid.

data.name: Exeggutor
data.flavorText: Each of its three heads has its own thoughts. When they want to go in different directions, Exeggutor becomes unable to move.

data.name: Pinsir
data.flavorText: One solid blow from its horns is enough to split apart a large tree. Its greatest rival in Alola is Vikavolt.

data.name: Hitmonchan
data.flavorText: While seeming to do nothing, it fires punches in lightning-fast volleys that are impossible to see.

data.name: Kabutops
data.flavorText: Its sleek shape is perfect for swimming. It slashes prey with its claws and drains the body fluids.

data.name: Tangela
data.flavorText: Many writhing vines cover it, so its true identity remains unknown. The blue vines grow its whole life long.

abilities.name: Call the Boss
abilities.text: When you play Giovanni's Persian from your hand, you may search your deck for the Trainer card named Giovanni, show it to your opponent, and put it into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward.

abilities.name: Water Immunity
abilities.text: You can't attach Water Energy cards from your hand to Articuno.

abilities.name: Sand Veil
abilities.text: Prevent all damage done to your Benched Pokémon by your opponent's attacks.

data.name: Gyarados
data.flavorText: Once it appears, it goes on a rampage. It remains enraged until it demolishes everything around it.

data.name: Weedle
data.flavorText: Often found in forests and grasslands. It has a sharp, toxic barb of around two inches on top of its head.

data.name: Caterpie

abilities.name: Adaptive Evolution
abilities.text: This Pokémon can evolve during your first turn or the turn you play it.

data.flavorText: For protection, it releases a horrible stench from the antenna on its head to drive away enemies.

data.name: Jigglypuff
data.flavorText: When its huge eyes light up, it sings a mysteriously soothing melody that lulls its enemies to sleep.
